Use Case 1 — Normal traffic

From web:
mysql -h 10.0.1.20 -u root -p
✅ Works (port 3306 allowed)


From web trying to SSH db:
ssh vagrant@10.0.1.20
❌ Blocked by firewall

Use Case 2 — Snort IDS detection
On fw:
sudo tail -f /var/log/syslog | grep snort

Then from web:
nmap -p 1-1024 10.0.1.20
✅ Snort will log scanning activity (if rule matches).



